what are bimonthly mortgage payments bimonthly mortgage payments would be paying twice a month there is a small savings in interest if you make payments a year but it's not huge the big savings is when you make a payment every week which gives you the equivalent of payments a year this will shave about years off of your mortgage depending on amount and interest rate some mortgage companies charge a fee to set this up for you i would not pay a fee as long as your mortgage company does not charge a penalty for prepayment you can send in a little extra with each payment and get the same results without paying a fee just take your monthly payment amount principle interest before escrow and divide by add that to each monthly payment and you get the equilivant of making a payment every weeks without extra charges from the credit card company i hope that helps Mortgage Credit card Government National Mortgage Association Taxation in the United States Insurance Primerica Financial Services Collateralized mortgage obligation Life insurance Student loan Bond Annual percentage rate Bank Mortgage-backed security Personal finance 401(k) Advance fee fraud Money Credit score Islamic banking Mutual fund Interest Virgin Mobile Annuity Refinancing Credit card fraud Treasury security United Kingdom corporation tax Social Security (United States) Savings and loan association Predatory lending Internet fraud Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corporation Subsidy Leasing Tertiary education fees in Australia FairTax Derivative (finance) Deflation (economics) Postage stamp Debt consolidation Taxation in the Republic of Ireland Security (finance) Real estate bubble Municipal bond Micropayment Cable television Schabir Shaik Trial E-ZPass GSM services Federal National Mortgage Association Octopus card Intellectual property Oyster card EFTPOS Housing cooperative Donald Trump Citigroup Futures contract Salary cap Actuarial notation Dividend Auto insurance National Insurance Universal life insurance Var